The Nigerian bourse extended its positive rally today, helped by price appreciation in MTN Nigeria (MTNN) and Dangote Cement (DANGCEM) stocks. Industrial Goods, Banking and Oil and Gas sector also recorded positive sentiment. The All Share Index (ASI) gained 844.74 absolute points, representing a growth of 2.88 percent to close at30,218.14 points. Similarly, Market Capitalization grew by N372.07 billion, representing an increase of 2.88 percent to close at N13.31 trillion. MTNN emerged the top gainer while LIVESTOCK emerged as top loser.  ENDURANCE OKAFOR